President Donald J. Trump and First Lady Melania Trump will host Prime Minister Shinzo Abe and Mrs. Akie Abe of Japan at the White House from April 26 to 27, 2019. The meeting will reaffirm the strong alliance between the United States and Japan and discuss efforts to achieve denuclearization in North Korea. The leaders will also explore ways to strengthen trade and investment relations and promote a free and open Indo-Pacific region. Additionally, the President and First Lady will visit Japan from May 25 to 28, 2019, following the enthronement of Emperor Naruhito, to deepen the bonds between the American and Japanese people and highlight the importance of the alliance.